  "body": "```\npragma solidity ^0.4.0;\n\ncontract BoolCast {\n\n    function foo() {\n\n        bool a;\n        int b;\n        uint c;\n        address d;\n        bytes32 e;\n\n        a = b != 0;     // a = bool(b);\n        a = c != 0;     // a = bool(c);\n        a = d != 0;     // a = bool(d);\n        a = e != 0;     // a = bool(e);\n    }\n\n}\n```\n\nIt's very easy to cast to bool by comparing to 0. Why can't bool() me made to do this?\n",
